# Regression (drop-128, 2026-07-24): a `flags` type at EXACTLY the 64-member cap — a bit-value is
# a u64, so `M63`'s value (`1 << 63`) is the last representable member. Proves the top-bit member
# round-trips correctly (a wrong `width_mask`/`msb_value` guard at the 64-bit boundary would
# misrepresent it) and stays disjoint from the bottom-bit member. Exit 0 on success.
name = "flags_64_members"
source = "src"

